## apcupsd CLIENT config — generated template (apctui)
##
## Install on a machine that draws power from a UPS managed by the apctui
## host. The client polls the server's NIS and shuts itself down on low
## battery. Replace {{MASTER_ADDR}} (e.g. 192.168.1.10:3551) and {{UPS_NAME}}.
##
## Deploy:
##   apt install apcupsd
##   scp this file -> /etc/apcupsd/apcupsd.conf
##   systemctl enable --now apcupsd
##
## Ordering note: clients must finish shutting down BEFORE the server host
## powers off / the UPS cuts output. These thresholds are deliberately more
## conservative than the server's (server: BATTERYLEVEL 10 / MINUTES 5).

UPSNAME {{UPS_NAME}}
UPSCABLE ether
UPSTYPE net
DEVICE {{MASTER_ADDR}}
POLLTIME 10

# shut down earlier than the server does
BATTERYLEVEL 15
MINUTES 8
TIMEOUT 0

# a client does not need to serve NIS; keep it off unless you chain monitors
NETSERVER off
